{{Quote|When we started to scout for locations we looked in various countries and cities, but Caserta was one of the most beautiful places on the planet and once we saw this, there was no question we wanted to shoot here.|[[George Lucas]]|<ref>''[[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace Scrapbook]]''</ref>}}
The '''Caserta Palace''' ([[Wikipedia:Italian|Italian]]: ''Reggia di Caserta''), located at {{Coor title dms|41|04|12|N|14|19|33|E|type:city}} is a palace in [[Wikipedia:Caserta|Caserta]], a town situated north-east of [[Wikipedia:Naples|Naples]]. Its Palazzo Reale is the largest royal palace in [[Wikipedia:Italy|Italy]] (and, by volume, in the world), designed by [[Wikipedia:Luigi Vanvitelli|Luigi Vanvitelli]] and built for the Bourbon King Charles III in the 1750s. It boasts over a thousand rooms and the surrounding park is full of fountains and statuary. There is also an English Garden.

The interior was used in filming the scenes in the [[Theed Royal Palace]] for [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] and again in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].

